column4: EU regulators say Qualcomm has not offered concessions in NXP bid
column5: BRUSSELS U.S. smartphone chipmaker Qualcomm  has not offered any concessions so far in its $38-billion bid for NXP Semiconductors   EU antitrust regulators said on Friday  increasing the risk of a lengthy investigation into the deal.

column4: EU regulators say Qualcomm has not offered concessions in NXP bid
column5: BRUSSELS  June 2 U.S. smartphone chipmaker Qualcomm has not offered any concessions so far in its $38-billion bid for NXP Semiconductors  EU antitrust regulators said on Friday  increasing the risk of a lengthy investigation into the deal.
